{"title_page": "Next Ukrainian parliamentary election", "text_new": "{{Infobox election\n| election_name = Next Ukrainian parliamentary election\n| country = Ukraine\n| type = parliamentary\n| ongoing = no\n| previous_election = 2019 Ukrainian parliamentary election\n| previous_year = 2019\n| next_election = \n| next_year = 2028<ref name=\"chesno.org/post/3402\"/>\n| seats_for_election = All 450 seats (possibly 300<ref name=\"639179IU450to300\"/>) in the [[Verkhovna Rada]]\n| majority_seats = 226 (possibly 151<ref name=\"639179IU450to300\"/>)\n| election_date = By 29 October 2023<ref name=\"chesno.org/post/3402\"/>\n<!--      Servant of the People (political party)      -->| image1 = \n| leader1 = [[Oleksandr Kornienko]]\n| leader_since1 = 27 May 2019\n| party1 = Servant of the People (political party)\n| last_election1 = '''254 seats, 43.16%'''\n| seats_needed1 = \n| seats1 = \n| seat_change1 =\n| popular_vote1 =\n| percentage1 =\n| swing1 =\n<!--     Opposition Platform \u2014 For Life      -->\n| image2 = [[File:Boiko Yurii Wiki Vadim Chuprina.jpg|center|75x75px]][[File:Vadim_Rabinovich2.jpeg|center|75x75px]]\n| leader2 = [[Yuriy Boyko]]<br>[[Vadim Rabinovich]]\n| leader_since2 = 26 May 2019\n| party2 = [[Opposition Platform \u2014 For Life]]\n| last_election2 = 43 seats, 13.05%\n| colour2 = 0050A3\n| seats2 =\n| seat_change2 =\n| popular_vote2 =\n| percentage2 =\n| swing2 =\n<!--      Fatherland      -->\n| image3 = [[File:Yulia Tymoshenko 2018 Vadim Chuprina (cropped).jpg|150x150px]]\n| leader3 = [[Yulia Tymoshenko]]\n| leader_since3 = 9 February 2001\n| party3 = All-Ukrainian Union \"Fatherland\"\n| last_election3 = 26 seats, 8.18%\n| seats3 =\n| seat_change3 =\n| popular_vote3 =\n| percentage3 =\n| swing3 =\n<!--      European Solidarity      -->\n| image4 = [[File:Official portrait of Petro Poroshenko.jpg|150x150px]]\n| leader4 = [[Petro Poroshenko]]\n| leader_since4 = 31 May 2019\n| party4 = European Solidarity\n| last_election4 = 25 seats, 8.10%\n| seats4 = \n| seat_change4 =\n| popular_vote4 =\n| percentage4 =\n| swing4 =\n <!--     Voice      -->\n| image5 = [[File:Svyatoslav Vakarchuk 2016.jpg|150x150px]]\n| leader5 = [[Svyatoslav Vakarchuk]]\n| leader_since5 = 16 May 2019\n| party5 = [[Voice (Ukrainian political party)|Voice]]\n| last_election5 = 20 seats, 5.82%\n| colour5 = Ed6C00\n| seats5 =\n| seat_change5 =\n| popular_vote5 =\n| percentage5 =\n| swing5 =\n<!--PM before/after-->\n| title = [[Prime Minister of Ukraine|Prime Minister]]\n| posttitle = Elected [[Prime Minister of Ukraine|Prime Minister]]\n| before_election = [[Denys Shmyhal]]\n| before_party = Independent politician\n| after_election = ''TBA''\n| after_party = \n}}\n\nAccording to the electoral Code of [[Ukraine]] the '''next Ukrainian parliamentary election''' will be held on the last Sunday of October of the fifth year of authority of the [[Verkhovna Rada|parliament]], if snap elections are not held.<ref name=\"633561ElectoralCode\">[https://en.interfax.com.ua/news/general/633561.html Electoral Code becomes effective in Ukraine], [[Interfax-Ukraine]] (1 January 2010)</ref> The [[2019 Ukrainian parliamentary election|previous parliamentary election]] in Ukraine were held on 21 July 2019.<ref name=\"2748306LPEUJ19\">[https://www.ukrinform.net/rubric-elections/2748306-cec-counts-100-percent-of-vote-in-ukraines-parliamentary-elections.html CEC counts 100 percent of vote in Ukraine's parliamentary elections], [[Ukrinform]] (26 July 2019)<br />{{in lang|ru}} [https://www.pravda.com.ua/rus/articles/2019/07/21/7221526/ Results of the extraordinary elections of the People's Deputies of Ukraine 2019], [[Ukrayinska Pravda]] (21 July 2019)</ref>\n\n==Electoral system==\nAccording to Art. 76 of the [[Constitution of Ukraine]] the term of office of Ukraine's parliament is five years.<ref name=\"chesno.org/post/3402\"/> Hence the powers of the [[9th Ukrainian Verkhovna Rada]] will formally expire in September 2024. So, the fifth, final year of the parliaments's powers will begin in September 2023.<ref name=\"chesno.org/post/3402\"/> According to Art. 77 of the Constitution, regular elections to the Verkhovna Rada take place on the last Sunday of October of the fifth year of parliamentary powers.<ref name=\"chesno.org/post/3402\"/> Thus, the next parliamentary elections are due to take place on 29 October 2023.<ref name=\"chesno.org/post/3402\">{{in lang|uk}} [https://www.chesno.org/post/3402/ Early to rejoice? Regular parliamentary elections may take place under Yanukovych's law], [[Civil movement \"Chesno\"]] (11 July 2019)</ref>\n\nOn 1 January 2020, the latest revision of the electoral code of Ukraine took effect.<ref name=\"633561ElectoralCode\"/> It states that deputies can only be elected on a party list in one nationwide constituency with a 5% [[election threshold]] with [[Open list|open]] regional lists of candidates for deputies.<ref name=\"633561ElectoralCode\"/> The new election law abolish the single-member constituencies system used in the [[2019 Ukrainian parliamentary election|2019 parliamentary election]].{{efn|Previous electoral reform passed in July 2019 also made all 450 members only elected by [[open list]] proportional representation; but it would not come into force until 1 December 2023.<ref name=EM20190712erU>[http://euromaidanpress.com/2019/07/12/ukraine-finally-gets-a-new-election-code-its-the-first-step-to-an-effective-political-system/ Ukraine finally gets a new Election Code. It\u2019s the first step to an effective political system] [[Euromaidan Press]], 12 July 2019</ref>}} In this election, the 450 members of the [[Verkhovna Rada]] were elected by two methods; 225 by [[closed list]] [[proportional representation]] in a nationwide constituency with a 5% threshold, and 225 in single-member constituencies by [[first-past-the-post voting]].<ref>[http://www.electionguide.org/elections/id/3163/ Ukraine] IFES</ref>\n\nOn 4 February 2020, parliament approved (with 236 votes) a Presidential bill to cut down the number of parliamentary deputies from 450 to 300.<ref name=\"639179IU450to300\"/> To do so, the [[Ukrainian Constitution]] needs to be altered, this will require at least 300 parliamentary votes.<ref name=\"639179IU450to300\">{{in lang|uk}} [https://ua.interfax.com.ua/news/political/639179.html The Verkhovna Rada has previously approved the reduction of the number of people's deputies to 300 and the transition to a proportional electoral system], [[Interfax-Ukraine]] (4 February 2020)</ref>\n\n==Opinion polls==\n{{main|Opinion polling for the next Ukrainian parliamentary election}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:95%;line-height:14px;\"\n! style=\"width:99px;\" rowspan=2 | Polling Firm/Link\n! style=\"width:150px;\" rowspan=2 | Last date<br>of polling\n! style=\"width:40px;\"| [[File:\u0417\u0435! \u0434\u0435\u043f\u0443\u0442\u0430\u0442 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0433\u0430 \u043d\u0430\u0440\u043e\u0434\u0443.svg|40px|link=Servant of the People (political party)]]\n! style=\"width:40px;\"| [[File:Logo of \"Opposition Platform - For life\".png|40px|link=Opposition Platform \u2014 For life]]\n! style=\"width:40px;\"| [[File:European Solidarity.svg|40px|link=European Solidarity]]\n! style=\"width:40px;\"| [[File:\u0412\u041e \u00ab\u0411\u0430\u0442\u044c\u043a\u0456\u0432\u0449\u0438\u043d\u0430\u00bb.png|40px|link=All-Ukrainian Union \"Fatherland\"]]\n! style=\"width:40px;\" |[[File:Strength and Honor (political party) Logo.jpg|40px|link=Strength and Honor (political party)]]\n! style=\"width:40px;\" |[[File:Holos.svg|40px|link=Voice (Ukrainian political party)]]\n! style=\"width:40px;\" |[[File:Radical Party Ukraine.png|40px|link=Radical Party of Oleh Lyashko]]\n! style=\"width:40px;\" |[[File:Svoboda logo-2.svg|40px|link=Svoboda (political party)]]\n! style=\"width:40px;\"| [[File:\u041b\u043e\u0433\u043e\u0442\u0438\u043f_\u043f\u0430\u0440\u0442\u0438\u0438_\u0428\u0430\u0440\u0438\u044f.svg|40px|link=Party of Shariy]]\n|-\n